    full_explanation: `An AI agent is an AI system that goes beyond answering questions — it can set sub-goals, use tools (like search or code execution), take actions in the real world, observe results, and iterate toward completing a complex task.\n\nUnlike a chatbot that responds to one question at a time, an agent receives a goal ("research this topic and write a report") and figures out how to accomplish it using available tools — searching the web, reading files, writing code, calling APIs — all without a human directing each step.\n\nAgents typically work in a loop: reason about what to do, take an action, observe the result, reason again, take another action, repeat until the goal is achieved. This is called a ReAct loop (Reasoning + Acting).\n\nAgents can use different "tools" depending on how they're configured: web search, code execution, database queries, email sending, file reading/writing, or any API you connect to them.`,
