    full_explanation: `The Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard released by Anthropic in November 2024 that defines how AI models connect to external tools, databases, file systems, and services. Before MCP, every AI integration required custom code for each tool-model combination. MCP standardizes the interface so that any MCP-compatible tool works with any MCP-compatible AI model without custom integration.\n\nThe protocol defines three main primitives: Resources (data the AI can read, like files or database records), Tools (actions the AI can take, like running a search or writing a file), and Prompts (reusable prompt templates).\n\nAn MCP server is a small program that exposes these primitives. You can build your own MCP server that exposes your company's database, CRM, or any internal system. Claude (via Claude Desktop) can then use those tools as naturally as it uses web search.\n\nMCP is rapidly becoming the standard: GitHub, Slack, Notion, Google Drive, and hundreds of other platforms have released MCP servers.`,
