    simple_definition: 'The basic unit AI models process text in — roughly a word or part of a word. Models charge per token.',
    full_explanation: `Language models don't process text word by word — they break text into tokens, which are chunks of characters. A token is roughly 3/4 of a word on average in English, meaning 100 tokens ≈ 75 words.\n\nCommon examples: "Hello" is 1 token. "Uncharacteristically" might be 2-3 tokens. "ChatGPT" is 3 tokens (Chat, G, PT). Numbers and special characters tokenize differently than English words.\n\nWhy it matters for you: AI API pricing is based on tokens (input tokens you send + output tokens the model generates). GPT-4o costs $2.50 per million input tokens and $10 per million output tokens. Most AI interactions cost fractions of a cent, but high-volume applications can see significant costs.\n\nContext window size is measured in tokens — a 128K context window can process about 96,000 words (roughly a full novel) in a single request. Longer inputs consume more tokens and cost more.`,
