    full_explanation: `A system prompt is a set of instructions provided to an AI model at the start of a session — before the user sends any messages. It defines how the model should behave, what persona to adopt, what topics to cover or avoid, and what format to use for responses.\n\nSystem prompts are invisible to end users (in most implementations) but have significant influence on model behavior. A well-written system prompt can turn a generic AI assistant into a specialized customer support agent, a coding assistant, or a writing tool with a specific voice.\n\nCommon elements: identity ("You are a customer support agent for Acme Corp"), capabilities ("You help with billing questions, account issues, and product troubleshooting"), constraints ("You do not discuss competitor products"), and format guidelines ("Always respond in a friendly, professional tone. Use bullet points for multi-step answers").\n\nSome models give system prompts higher authority than user messages — meaning a system prompt constraint can override what a user asks. This is important for building safe, controlled AI products.`,
