    full_explanation: `Text-to-speech (TTS) is AI technology that converts written text into spoken audio. Modern AI TTS systems produce natural, human-like speech with appropriate pacing, intonation, and emotional expression — far beyond the robotic voices of older TTS systems.\n\nThe quality spectrum ranges from basic (Google's built-in TTS, decent but robotic) to premium (ElevenLabs, which passes the "is this a human?" test for most listeners in blind tests).\n\nKey features to evaluate in TTS: naturalness (does it sound human?), voice options (variety of voices, genders, accents), language support (how many languages with native-quality pronunciation?), emotional control (can you adjust sadness, enthusiasm, formality?), and API quality (how easy to integrate into applications?).\n\nElevenLabs is currently the quality leader for general TTS. OpenAI's TTS API is cheaper and good quality. Google Cloud TTS covers more languages. Amazon Polly is cheap and reliable for basic use cases.\n\nCommon applications: YouTube voiceovers, podcast production, e-learning narration, accessibility features, customer service IVR systems, and any content that needs audio without live recording.`,
